    "(3) Meta proposed a unified meta learning framework for both zeroand few-shot event detection, which is designed to exploit prompt tuning and contrastive learning for quick adaptation to unseen tasks.",
    "In the article of MetaEvent, for,the instances of support set and query set are both N × K of each epoch.",
    "That is different with our settings and our query set instances is N × 1.",
    "Another important point is that from the code provided by the author of MetaEvent, it can be seen that during model validation and testing, the model still participates in gradient updates when the support set input to the model, which is different from our validation and testing strategy.",
    "For a fair comparison, we have modified the validation and testing code to not participate in gradient updates."
